hands_on_practices.solution:
We have $f(u,v)=(x(u,v),y(u,v))$ with
$$x(u,v)=u\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}},\quad y(u,v)=v\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}.$$
1. Compute partial derivatives:
$$\frac{\partial x}{\partial u}
=\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}},\quad
\frac{\partial x}{\partial v}
=u\,\frac{d}{dv}\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}}
=u\cdot\frac{1}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}}}\bigl(-v\bigr)
=-\frac{u\,v}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}}},$$
$$\frac{\partial y}{\partial v}
=\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}},\quad
\frac{\partial y}{\partial u}
=v\,\frac{d}{du}\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}
=v\cdot\frac{1}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}}\bigl(-u\bigr)
=-\frac{u\,v}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}}.$$
2. Form the Jacobian matrix and its determinant:
$$J(u,v)=\begin{vmatrix}
\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}} & -\dfrac{u\,v}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}}}\\
-\dfrac{u\,v}{2\sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}} & \sqrt{1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}}
\end{vmatrix}
=\sqrt{\bigl(1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}\bigr)}
-\frac{u^2v^2}{4\sqrt{\bigl(1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}\bigr)}}.$$
3. Combine terms over a common denominator:
$$J(u,v)
=\frac{4\bigl(1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}\bigr)-u^2v^2}
{4\sqrt{\bigl(1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}\bigr)}}
=\frac{2 - u^2 - v^2}{2\sqrt{\bigl(1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{v^2}{2}\bigr)}}.$$
4. Evaluate at $(u,v)=(\tfrac12,\tfrac12)$:
$$u^2=v^2=\tfrac14,\quad
2 - u^2 - v^2=2-\tfrac14-\tfrac14=\tfrac32,\quad
1-\tfrac{u^2}{2}=1-\tfrac{1}{8}=\tfrac78.$$
Hence
$$J\!\bigl(\tfrac12,\tfrac12\bigr)
=\frac{\tfrac32}{2\sqrt{\tfrac78\cdot\tfrac78}}
=\frac{\tfrac32}{2\cdot\tfrac78}
=\frac{\tfrac32}{\tfrac74}
=\frac{6}{7}.$$
